main event: Several UFO sightings were reported near Waskish, Minnesota in 1952, including a bright reddish-orange object observed by the ground observer corps, an object resembling a polished aluminum meteor, and an ellipsoid-shaped object with a dome on top trailing another unidentified object.
interesting points: The bright object was observed to accelerate vertically and disappear suddenly.
The polished aluminum object traveled at around 30 miles per hour and had no visible means of propulsion.
One of the observed objects was described as ellipsoid-shaped with a dome on top, giving off a bright light and appearing to trail another unidentified object.
The report noted no sound accompanying the sightings of the UFOs.
